article_title: Big Sioux River Overtaken By Ducks
article_text:
Sioux Falls, SD

The Sioux Falls Downtown Duck Derby made its debut at the Downtown River Greenway today.

Thousands of adopted ducks made their way down the Big Sioux River, with proceeds going to South Dakota Voices for Children.

According to their website, over 4,000 ducks were adopted. If you couldn't make out there and would still like to donate, just click the link.
